To Paul (letter): Lie-Liechen writes two sheets and I write two sheets;
--> she tells about the difficulties that prevented her from answering, describing specifically a day's schedule; then she turns to the lawsuit and reveals a few things that must be unknown to him. I present an outline of responsibilities as evidence of my intention to write a letter, then develop my opinion about the phase of history in which millions of bourgeois citizens face millions of workers, fight Marxism and praise aristocratism
as the only effective means of dampening the millions in their fruitless voracity for idleness.
